New Jersey Devils star forward Jack Hughes reportedly cut his hand during a team dinner and is expected to miss the team's upcoming game against the Washington Capitals.
Shohei Ohtani is nearly without peer in MLB after his latest Most Valuable Player Award, so it's time to look to other leagues for comparison, too.
An NHL fans treated Colorado Avalanche fans to a wild beer-chugging moment in the third period of their 4-1 over the Anaheim Ducks on Tuesday.
The Washington Capitals picked up a 4-1 victory over the Carolina Hurricanes on Tuesday night, but it came with some black-and-blues in Raleigh, North Carolina.
Buffalo Sabres captain Rasmus Dahlin is taking an indefinite leave from the team to support his fiancée Carolina Matovac's heart transplant recovery in Sweden.
Jordan Binnington joked that he “had an assist" on Alex Ovechkin’s 900th goal. The St. Louis Blues goalie later said he fully intended to return the milestone puck.
St. Louis Blues goaltender Jordan Binnington was caught red-handed trying to pocket Alex Ovechkin's 900th career goal on Wednesday night.
Alex Ovechkin scored his 900th NHL goal after breaking Wayne Gretzky's record in April, becoming the league's first player to reach this historic milestone.
NHL player Arthur Kaliyev accused of $50,000 fraud scheme targeting girlfriend to fund gambling addiction, using fake checks and intimidation tactics.
Florida Panthers forward Brad Marchand stepped away to coach his friend’s U18 team in Halifax, honoring the memory of his friend’s 10-year-old daughter, Selah.
U.S. hockey star Brady Tkachuk discussed President Donald Trump's locker room call before the 4 Nations Face-Off final and its impact heading into the Olympics.
Former NHL star Ryan Kesler faces criminal sexual conduct charges in Michigan court, pleading not guilty to misdemeanor counts from alleged January incident.
A hockey fan fell from the upper concourse at PPG Paints Arena in Pittsburgh on Monday night during the Penguins' three-goal win over the St. Louis Blues.
The arrests of Miami Heat guard Terry Rozier and Portland Trail Blazers head coach Chauncey Billups are the latest chapter in gambling scandals in sports.
Florida Panthers star Brad Marchand broke down in tears as the Boston Bruins played a tribute video for him in his first game back at the TD Garden.
The San Jose Sharks were forced to apologize on Saturday after displaying a pro-U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement message on its video board.
The Chicago Blackhawks announced Wednesday that team captain Nick Foligno has taken a leave of absence to be with his daughter as she undergoes a heart surgery procedure.
Philadelphia sports fans suffered a rare blow as the Phillies, Eagles and Flyers all lost on the same night — the first time that’s happened since 1983.
Who will win the Stanley Cup at the end of the season? Let's take a look at the odds now that the new NHL season has started.
Los Angeles Kings winger Jeff Malott stepped up to spar with Colorado Avalanche defenseman Josh Manson after a huge hit delivered to Kings forward Warren Foegele.
The NHL doled out punishment on Monday after the preseason finale between the Florida Panthers and Tampa Bay Lightning saw 65 penalties and 312 penalty minutes.
ESPN broadcaster Ben McDonald wasn't committing to watching any NHL c coverage this month and expressed it during an MLB Postseason game on Wednesday.
Minnesota Wild superstar Kirill Kaprizov has signed a record-breaking $136 million deal, carrying an average annual value of $17 million.
Hockey Hall of Fame goalie Bernie Parent, who led the Philadelphia Flyers to their only two Stanley Cup titles in the 1970s, has died at age 80.
Sabres captain Rasmus Dahlin said in an open letter to fans that his fiancée received a life-saving heart transplant after suffering major heart failure during the offseason.
The hockey world mourned the loss of minor leaguer Orca Wiesblatt, who died following a car accident in Canada early Sunday morning. He was 25.
The legendary 1980 "Miracle on Ice" hockey team moved closer to receiving Congressional Gold Medals on Monday as the House passed the "Miracle on Ice Congressional Gold Medal Act."
Ken Dryden, a Hall of Fame goaltender who won six Stanley Cups with the Montreal Canadiens and later became a broadcaster, has died at 78 after a battle with cancer.
The 'Ruthless' podcast crew discusses why fans are outraged over NFL RedZone commercials on 'The Will Cain Show.'
Nearly one year after Johnny and Matthew Gaudreau were killed by an alleged drunk driver, their widows speak about final goodbyes and raising children without fathers.
